-- Lexer error: `_` is a digit separator in Medaka INTEGER literals (`1_000`,
-- `0xD_EAD`) but NOT inside `\u{…}`, and this fixture pins that DECIDED fork (#592).
-- It used to be an S0: `uHexEnd` stops at the first non-hex-digit and never checked
-- WHAT stopped it, so `4` became the whole codepoint (a fabricated U+0004) and `1}`
-- fell through into the string as literal DATA — `"a\u{4_1}b"` printed the bytes
-- 61 04 31 7d 62 at exit 0, with no diagnostic.
-- Rejecting is the reversible direction: this could be widened later to MEAN `\u{41}`
-- without breaking any program, whereas accepting it could never be walked back.
x = "a\u{4_1}b"
